Turning Point Brands, Inc. Key Developments

Turning Point Brands Mulls Acquisitions
Jun 30 17
Turning Point Brands, Inc. (NYSE:TPB) is seeking acquisitions. Turning Point Brands, Inc. has filed a Shelf Registration in the amount of $200 million. Turning Point will use the net proceeds for general corporate purposes, including working capital, repayment of indebtedness, acquisitions and other business purposes.


Turning Point Brands, Inc. Presents at Jefferies 2017 Global Consumer Conference, Jun-20-2017 04:00 PM
Jun 9 17
Turning Point Brands, Inc. Presents at Jefferies 2017 Global Consumer Conference, Jun-20-2017 04:00 PM. Venue: White Elephant Hotel, Nantucke, Massachusetts, United States. Speakers: James M. Murray, Senior Vice President of Business Planning, Larry Wexler, President and Chief Executive Officer, Mark Stegeman, Chief Financial & Accounting Officer and Senior Vice President.


Turning Point Brands, Inc. Announces Consolidated Financial Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 11 17
Turning Point Brands, Inc. announced consolidated financial results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net sales of $66.788 million against $49.866 million a year ago. Operating income was $10.757 million against $10.909 million a year ago. Loss before income taxes was $0.178 million against income of $2.447 million a year ago. Net income was $1.877 million against $2.234 million a year ago. Diluted earnings per common share were $0.10 against $0.27 a year ago. EBITDA was $11.400 million against $11.202 million a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $13.638 million against $12.453 million a year ago. Net Debt was $225.2 million against $215.3 million as on December 31, 2016. Net cash used in operating activities was $2.340 million against net cash provided by operating activities of $0.977 million a year ago. Capital expenditures were $0.368 million against $0.454 million a year ago.


